The paper proposes a neural document dating system that utilizes attention-based models to predict the creation time of documents. This task involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques, which are commonly studied in the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), information retrieval (cs.IR), and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper utilizes deep learning models (cs.DL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques to improve the accuracy of the proposed system.
